After a disastrous first night Cletus meets them in the morning accompanied by his cretinous cousins Horace and Elmer, who take the gang to their “Muckman Mooseum” on the edge of a nearby swamp. Various Muckman artifacts, including a Muckman skull under glass, are on display. More convincing is the unearthly howl the crew hears outside the museum. Giving chase, the gang sees a hirsute figure fleeing through the woods (leaving behind the unbearable stench characteristic of Muckman), capturing a glimpse of the creature on tape. That night they get an even better look at the monster when it attacks their cabin, and the following evening when the crew attempts to document the capture of the creature in a trap set by Cletus and his boys all hell breaks loose. The creature appears big as life. Chaos ensues, there is blood and dismemberment, but all is not as it seems. Cletus and his gang have their own agenda, as do Mickey and Asia, and even Billie knows more than she lets on. In the end there are more things loose in the woods than anyone suspects, and the swamps unleash a few secrets as well.

programme.title: Redemption On A Public Land Stud, Gavin's Bowhunting Journey
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we tag along with Midwest Whitetail editor Gavin Koterba as he takes us through a multi year quest that ends with him tagging his biggest buck to date. After making the move to Iowa to chase his dream, Gavin's goal has been to shoot a buck on public land. With years of scouting under his belt, multiple encounters with giant bucks, and an attitude to learn as much as possible along the way, hopes were extremely high going into the 2023 deer season. Follow along on the roller coaster ride that ultimately ends in Gavin tagging his biggest buck ever. As always, we can't say thank you enough for the continued support and hope you have a great rest of the deer season!

programme.title: Two Perfect Hunts With The Reed Family, Reading The Christmas Story
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we bring you a show that has a little bit of everything. Kicking things off, we join Chad Holmes who reads us the Christmas Story and discusses the true meaning of Christmas. Following that we join Mike and Bella Reed who bring us up to speed on what has been happening in the woods since Mike tagged out on "Fitzmagic" back in November. Finally, we join the Reed family during the shotgun seasons as two perfect hunts unfold on the same bean field. Up first is Kathryn Reed who makes it to the woods for her first hunt of the year. With the wrong wind direction to hunt the current Redneck Blind setup, Mike gets mobile and moves a trailer blind into place. The move pays off BIG and Kathryn has the perfect hunt and builds another memory. Then, we jump to the same field only a few days later with Brynn Reed who's hoping to pull off the same feat as her mom! Little did she know the biggest buck of her life would walk into the field and after following her shooting process, a perfectly placed bullet closes the chapter on a true surprise buck. As always, thank you from all of us at Midwest Whitetail for taking the time to watch and for supporting us this entire season. Merry Christmas to each and every one of you and good luck the next time you hit the woods!

programme.title: Hunting Intern Chases A Dream, Jenna Makes A Perfect Shot On A Giant 8
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we kick things off joining Drake Lamb, Justin Karns and sister Jenna in southern Iowa. With a great food source to hunt, the trio key in on a big 8 that has been frequenting the area with hopes of trying to fill Jenna's first buck tag of the season. After hunting her tail off all fall, she finally gets her opportunity and makes a perfect shot. Next, Josh Sparks joins us with an important announcement about the opening or the Midwest Whitetail internship opportunity for the upcoming 2024 season. If you are interested in applying, be sure to visit our social media pages for more information that will be released soon! Finally, on the topic of interns, we shift our focus to catching up with Shea McTighe who was a part of the 2023 internship class here at Midwest Whitetail. Shea talks through why he was interested in the internship, what he learned throughout his time here, and generally speaking talks through his take aways while here. After putting in a ton of work throughout the season following Kaleb Greiner with a camera and maintaining editing tasks, Shea's hunting opportunity arose during the 2nd shotgun season in Iowa and as you'll see, he made the most of it.
